img.closest('li') 

element.closest()

database returns a firebase reference

Once you've firebase reference, you can do .set and .on


1. Get the reference from the library
2. write .set()
3. Read .on()


.set() takes one argument (in JSON), no need to convert to strings

.on() takes 2 args, 1st is string and the second is callback function
-callback function will be called when the value in the firebase changes
-callback variable is a firebase snapshot
